&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center;&#34;&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;/publication/32834114&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;32834114&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center;&#34;&gt;
In order to fight this disease, a new coumarin derivative ligand (4-[(pyridin-3-ylmethyl) amino]-2H-chromen-2-one) (LTA) has been synthesized and characterized by single-crystal X-ray diffraction, NMR, ATR, UV-Visible and cyclic voltammetry. […] The possible binding mode between LTA and Main protease (Mpro) of SARS-CoV-2 and their reactivity were studied using molecular docking simulation. […] Single crystal X-ray diffraction showed that LTA crystallizes in a monoclinic system with P2 1 space group. […] The reactivity descriptors such as nucleophilic index confirm that LTA is more nucleophile, inducing complexation with binding species like biomolecules. […] The binding energy of the SARS-CoV-2/Mpro-LTA complex and the calculated inhibition constant using docking simulation showed that the active LTA molecule has the ability to inhibit SARS-CoV-2.
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center;&#34;&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;/publication/32870469&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;32870469&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center;&#34;&gt;
This prospective study was undertaken in critically ill patients to evaluate the reliability of single negative real-time polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) in lower tracheal aspirates (LTA) in predicting a second negative test and to analyze clinical factors potentially influencing the viral shedding. […] From April 9, 2020 onwards, intubated COVID-19 patients treated in the intensive care unit were systematically evaluated for severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) by RT-PCR of nasopharyngeal swabs and LTA. […] The time to negativity was defined as the time between the onset of symptoms and the viral clearance in LTA. […] In critically ill COVID-19 patients, one negative LTA should be sufficient to assess and exclude infectivity.
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
